Write key-value pair with metadata  Write a value identified by a key. Use URL-encoding to use special characters (for example, :, !, %) in the key name. Body should be the value to be stored along with JSON metadata to be associated with the key/value pair. Existing values, expirations, and metadata will be overwritten. If neither expiration nor expiration_ttl is specified, the key-value pair will never expire. If both are set, expiration_ttl is used and expiration is ignored.     $response   =   $client  ->  workers  ()  ->  kv  ()  ->  writeKeyWithMetadata  (  'account_id'  ,   'namespace_id'  ,   'key_name'  );
